---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  titulo="Privacy Policy · LRA Cloud Operations"
  descripcion="Privacy policy for LRA Cloud Operations. Learn how we collect, use and protect your data when you contact us through our website."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden" style="background-color: #0A2540;">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-40"
      style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(147,184,255,0.15) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 28px 28px;"
    >
    </div>
    <div
      class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-6 py-20 sm:py-24 text-center"
    >
      <span
        class="inline-flex items-center text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-6"
        style="background: rgba(30,111,255,0.2); color: #93b8ff; border: 1px solid rgba(30,111,255,0.25);"
      >
        Legal
      </span>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-white mb-5"
        style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base" style="color: rgba(147,184,255,0.6);">
        Last updated: June 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div
        class="prose prose-gray max-w-none
        prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-headings:tracking-tight
        prose-h2:text-xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4
        prose-p:text-gray-600 prose-p:leading-relaxed
        prose-a:text-[#1E6FFF] prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline
        prose-ul:text-gray-600 prose-li:leading-relaxed"
      >
        <h2>1. Who collects your data</h2>
        <p>
          The data controller is <strong>LRA Cloud Operations</strong> (operated by
          Ruben Alexis Liquenson), reachable at
          <a href="mailto:info@lracloudops.com">info@lracloudops.com</a>. This
          policy applies to data submitted through the contact form at <strong
            >lracloudops.com</strong
          >.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
        <p>When you submit the contact form we collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Full name</li>
          <li>Business email address</li>
          <li>Engagement type and estimated scope (if provided)</li>
          <li>Message content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not collect payment information, health data, or any special
          category data under GDPR Article 9.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Why we collect it</h2>
        <p>
          Data submitted through the contact form is used solely to respond to
          your inquiry and assess whether we can help with your project. We do
          not use this data for marketing, profiling, or third-party
          advertising.
        </p>
        <p>
          Legal basis: legitimate interest (GDPR Article 6(1)(f)) — responding
          to a direct inquiry from the data subject.
        </p>

        <h2>4. How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          Inquiry data is retained for up to 12 months after the last
          communication. If no engagement is established, data is deleted after
          this period.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Third-party processors</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Web3Forms</strong> — processes form submissions and routes them
            to our inbox. Form data passes through their servers. See <a
              href="https://web3forms.com/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Web3Forms Privacy Policy</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> — CAPTCHA verification to prevent
            spam. No personal data is stored by Turnstile. See <a
              href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Privacy Policy</a
            >.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — privacy-first, cookieless
            analytics. No personal data or IP addresses are stored. Data is aggregated
            and anonymous.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Analytics 4 (GA4)</strong> — measures aggregate traffic patterns
            (pages visited, session duration, referral source). GA4 uses cookies and
            may process your IP address. No data is shared with advertising networks.
            Data is retained for 14 months. See <a
              href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a
            >. You can opt out via <a
              href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a
            >.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p>
          Google Analytics 4 sets first-party cookies (<code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_*</code>)
          to distinguish unique visitors and sessions. These cookies expire after 2 years
          and 13 months respectively.
        </p>
        <p>
          Beyond GA4 cookies, the site uses two <code>localStorage</code> keys that contain
          no personal data and are never sent to any server:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>announcement-dismissed</code> — remembers if you closed the announcement bar.</li>
          <li><code>lang-preference</code> — remembers your selected interface language.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Your rights under GDPR</h2>
        <p>
          If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have the right
          to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold
            about you.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Rectification</strong> — correct inaccurate or incomplete data.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your data ("right to be
            forgotten").
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable
            format.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Objection</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate
            interests.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, email us at
          <a href="mailto:info@lracloudops.com">info@lracloudops.com</a>. We
          will respond within 30 days.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Data security</h2>
        <p>
          All data transmitted to this site is encrypted in transit (HTTPS
          enforced via HSTS). The site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages with strict
          security headers including Content Security Policy, X-Frame-Options
          and Permissions-Policy.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy periodically. Material changes will be
          reflected in the "Last updated" date above. Continued use of the site
          after changes constitutes acceptance.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For any privacy-related question or request:
          <a href="mailto:info@lracloudops.com">info@lracloudops.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 items-start sm:items-center justify-between"
      >
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors"
          style="color: #64748b;"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-4 h-4"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke="currentColor"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              stroke-width="2"
              d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
          </svg>
          Back to home
        </a>
        <a
          href="/terms"
          class="text-sm font-semibold transition-colors"
          style="color: #1E6FFF;"
        >
          Terms of Service →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
